'''WMTQ''' is a [[Catholic]] radio station broadcasting from [[Elmira, New York]]. WMTQ is located at 88.1 on the FM dial. Part of ''[[The Station of the Cross]]'', WMTQ is owned and operated by [[Holy Family Communications]] which also owns and operates several other stations. The call letters represent Mary the Queen, to whom this station is dedicated. [[The Station of the Cross]] relies on the [http://www.ewtn.com/radio/ EWTN Global Catholic Radio Network] for the bulk of its programming.
==History== [[WHOM]] had the '''WMTQ''' [[callsign]] from 1973<ref name="by1974">{{cite book|title=Broadcasting Yearbook 1974|year=1974|page=B-132|url=http://www.davidgleason.com/Archive%20BC-YB/1974/B%202%201974%20YB.pdf|format=PDF|accessdate=February 23, 2010}}</ref> until it became [[WHOM]] in 1976.<ref name="by1977">{{cite book|title=Broadcasting Yearbook 1977|year=1977|page=C-132|url=http://www.davidgleason.com/Archive%20BC-YB/1977/C-2%20Radio%20Broadcasting%20Yearbook%201977.pdf|format=PDF|accessdate=February 23, 2010}}</ref>
"On October 29, 2010, the Dominican Monastery of Mary the Queen filed an application with the Federal Communications Commission to obtain permission to assign to Holy Family Communications its Permit to Construct a Noncommercial Educational Radio Station, WMTQ, to serve Elmira, NY and surrounding areas. The application proposes a Class A FM station operating at 236 meters Above Ground Level with .09 kW ERP from 42-6-21.7 N and 76-52-17.1 W."<ref>Legal notice published from 11/21/2010 to 11/29/2010 on [http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:4x9iDRcCyOoJ:classifieds.star-gazette.com/osform/MVCCService%3Fosform_template%3D/standard/resultDetail.oft%26publication%3Dstargaz%26netgravityPublication%3D%26category%3DLegalLegalNotices%26startElement%3D0%26displayCount%3D6%26selectedCount%3D25%26sortOrder%3Dascending%26sortAttribute%3DadDescription%26displayArguments%3Dsummary%257CID%26queryString%3D%26queryResultCount%3D62%26queryValues%3DSm..%26clickedButton%3DviewPrev+WMTQ+class&cd=39&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=us&client=firefox-a&source=www.google.com Star-Gazette.com;] cached image retrieved via Google 13 February 2011.</ref>
WMTQ's website is [http://www.wmtq.org/ www.wmtq.org.]
